 quarrels — a harmless nickname — but we must be serious now. Come, let us go back to our colleagues and do our duty.'



Dr Azureus, whose oratorical zest seemed to have waned, briefly informed his audience that the declaration which all had to read and sign, had been typed in the same number of copies as there would be signatures. He had been given to understand, he said, that this would lend a dash of individuality to every copy. What was the real object of this arrangement he did not exp